# Openable File Paths In Chat

Whenever you share a file (especially `.md`) or a filesystem path with the user,
make it openable from this Cursor session. Do not leave bare unlinked path text
as the only reference.

## Required format

1. Use a **markdown link** whose target is a path Cursor can resolve in this
   workspace.
2. Prefer an **absolute workspace path** as the link target
   (e.g. `/agent/repos/PLX_MC/docs/FOO.md`).
3. Link text may be the basename or a short label
   (e.g. `[SPEC.md](/agent/repos/PLX_MC/.orchestrator/.../SPEC.md)`).
4. If you mention several files, **each** gets its own openable link.
5. Code citations for regions still use the `startLine:endLine:filepath`
   citation format; this rule covers narrative path sharing, not citation
   blocks.

## Examples

Good:

- Draft SPEC: [SPEC.md](/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/platform/2026-07-24-ds-gov-cloud-enforcement/SPEC.md)
- Kickoff report: [REPORT.md](/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/platform/2026-07-24-ds-gov-cloud-enforcement/REPORT.md)

Bad:

- SPEC is at `artifacts/platform/.../SPEC.md` (no openable link)
- See the SPEC in the orchestrator folder (no path)
